From 2333cb06d339b1198da913acd873ac88f39c49e7 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Timothy Day <timday@thelustrecollective.com>
Date: Thu, 18 Jun 2026 22:48:53 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] LU-18986 mgc: fix OOB read registering targets with numeric
 NIDs

mgc_target_register() has a KASAN slab-out-of-bounds read
when registering a target whose NIDs are legacy NIDs while
the MGS connection has OBD_CONNECT_MGS_NIDLIST:

  BUG: KASAN: slab-out-of-bounds in mgc_target_register+0x8a1/0x1750 [mgc]
  Read of size 64 at addr ffff88803eb811c0 by task lustre-ktest/1751

server_lsi2mti() only allocates and fills the string NID list
mti_nidlist[] when the target has large NIDs (LDD_F_LARGE_NID); for
legacy NIDs it stores them in mti_nids[].

However, the new registration protocol path was entered whenever the
export had OBD_CONNECT_MGS_NIDLIST set, regardless of whether the mti
actually carried a string NID list. It then read NIDLIST_SIZE() bytes
from mti->mti_nidlist[], running off the end of the allocation.

The MGS server side already supports receiving the NIDs in the mti
body with an empty nidlist header.

Gate the nidlist transfer on large_nids. When the MGS supports the
nidlist protocol but the target has numeric NIDs, send an empty
nidlist header and leave the NIDs in the mti body; the MGS reads
them from mti_nids[] via its compatibility path.

Fixes: e9c290e7dd2e ("LU-18986 mgc: client part of new registration protocol")
Signed-off-by: Timothy Day <timday@thelustrecollective.com>
Change-Id: Ic77d7dc3da8160d22d07657d1c7733330541cbe3
---
 lustre/mgc/mgc_request_server.c | 6 +++---
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/lustre/mgc/mgc_request_server.c b/lustre/mgc/mgc_request_server.c
index 1f01e28c232e..22abec0a263d 100644
--- a/lustre/mgc/mgc_request_server.c
+++ b/lustre/mgc/mgc_request_server.c
@@ -202,7 +202,7 @@ static int mgc_target_register(struct obd_export *exp,
 	if (!req)
 		RETURN(-ENOMEM);
 
-	if (large_nids || nidlist) {
+	if (large_nids) {
 		bufsize = MGS_MAXREQSIZE - sizeof(struct ptlrpc_body) -
 			  sizeof(*mti) - sizeof(*mtn);
 		avail = bufsize / MTN_NIDSTR_SIZE;
@@ -210,7 +210,7 @@ static int mgc_target_register(struct obd_export *exp,
 		nidlist_size = 0;
 	}
 
-	if (nidlist) {
+	if (nidlist && large_nids) {
 		if (mti->mti_nid_count <= avail) { /* inline buffer */
 			req_capsule_set_size(&req->rq_pill,
 					     &RMF_MGS_TARGET_NIDLIST,
@@ -270,7 +270,7 @@ static int mgc_target_register(struct obd_export *exp,
 		}
 		desc->bd_frag_ops->add_iov_frag(desc, mti->mti_nidlist,
 						nidlist_size);
-	} else if (nidlist) {
+	} else if (nidlist && large_nids) {
 		mtn->mtn_nids = mti->mti_nid_count;
 		memcpy(mtn->mtn_inline_list, mti->mti_nidlist, nidlist_size);
 	} else if (large_nids) {
